    "id": "f_csv_03e4e9188f",
    "slug": "we-read-novels-because-we-need-stories-we-crave-them-we-can-t-live-without-tel",
    "texto": "We read novels because we need stories; we crave them; we can’t live without telling them and hearing them. Stories are how we make sense of our lives and of the world. When we’re distressed and go to therapy, our therapist’s job is to help us tell our story. Life doesn’t come with plots; it’s messy and chaotic; life is one damn, inexplicable thing after another. And we can’t have that. We insist on meaning. And so we tell stories so that our lives make sense.",
